Foxes are small-to-medium-sized omnivorous mammals belonging to several genera of the family
 Canidae. They have a flattened skull; upright, triangular ears; a pointed, slightly upturned snout;
 and a long, bushy tail.

)Rabbits are small mammals in the family Leporidae.Rabbits are small, furry mammals with long ears,
 short fluffy tails, and strong, large hind legs. They have 2 pairs of sharp incisors (front teeth),
 one pair on top and one pair on the bottom. They also have 2 peg teeth behind the top incisors.
